(18, 'en', '<div class="Section1">\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:\r\nnormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:14.0pt;font-family:Verdana;\r\nmso-ansi-language:EN-US">Welcome to the conference site!<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:30.6pt"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:EN-US">Annual Ukrainian Conference\r\non Space Research, held at the <st1:placename w:st="on">National</st1:placename>\r\n<st1:placetype w:st="on">Center</st1:placetype> management and testing of space\r\nvehicles (NCSVCT), located near the <span class="SpellE">Eupatoria</span> town\r\n(Crimea) on the <st1:place w:st="on">Black Sea</st1:place> coast.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:30.6pt"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:30.6pt"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:EN-US"><span style="mso-tab-count:\r\n1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Our conference is devoted to a wide range of scientific space\r\nresearch, which combines by the following criteria– these studies are conducted\r\n(or closely related studies that are conducted) using the spacecraft.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:30.6pt"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:30.6pt"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:EN-US"><span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp;</span>The traditional headings of the conference\r\nare:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN-US">- Investigation of near space (the Sun, the solar-terrestrial\r\ninteractions, magnetosphere, ionosphere, etc.)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN-US">- The Earth observation from the space<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN-US">- Space Biology<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN-US">- Microgravity Science<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN-US"><span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp;</span>- Equipment, materials and\r\ntechnologies for space exploration<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:30.6pt"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:EN-US">The next twelfth Ukrainian\r\nConference on Space Research, will be held during September 3-7, 2012. To\r\nobtain more detailed information or to register for the conference see the page\r\n<b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><u><span style="color:#00CCFF">12\r\nConference</span></u></b>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN-US">On the <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><u><span style="color:\r\n#00CCFF">Archive</span></u></b> page there are abstracts of previous\r\nconferences, and some beautiful photos.</span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-ansi-language:EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n'),
